      "writtenOn": "2021-05-05T18:51:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for catching this. Note that Run doesn\u0027t have a trigger time, only CLs do; and taking another look, it looks like Run.CreateTime should actually correspond to Attempt.StartTime.\n\n   // For non-API triggered Run, the CreateTime is the timestamp of the last\n   // vote on a Gerrit CL that triggers this Run.\n   CreateTime time.Time `gae:\",noindex\"`\n\nFrom https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/main:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/cv/internal/run/model.go;l\u003d55\n\n  def attempt_start(self):\n    \"\"\"datetime.datetime of the most recently triggered candidate CL.\"\"\"\n    return self.cls[0].triggered_at\n\nFrom https://chrome-internal.googlesource.com/infra/infra_internal/+/master/infra_internal/services/cq/pending_manager/base.py#282\n\nAnd reading https://crbug.com/1105669, I thought we actually wanted to change the meaning of Attempt.StartTime, so that after the CV change StartTime would change to mean processing start time, and CreateTime would be added to mean trigger time?",
      "parentUuid": "50df0b03_1b5a1a24",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 92,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 94,
        "endChar": 70
      },
      "revId": "b1f6e14b089006104dead40ecd7aae88af80b542",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
